Description: Ecology Crossroads is an innovative charity using climate finance to create tax-exempt portfolios with Indigenous philanthropy and forests.
Full Description: Ecology Crossroads is a nonprofit charitable organization founded in 1994 to confront climate change and provide ecosystem services through program activities and events it coordinates with corporate and organization sponsors. The organization earned a reputation in the final decade of the millenia distributing 10 million trees across the United States for Arbor Day and organizing large scale expositions and fairs for Earth Day. In January of 2020 the organization restated it articles of incorporation, it was subsequently reinstated as a 501(c)(3) nonprofit and authorized by the IRS with charitable foundation status under section 509(a)(1). In 2022 the organization began the soft-launch of a carbon finance tool (instrument) that can serve as an investment portfolio product with Payment for Ecosystem Services Contracts through its subsidiary, Globcal International. Through MRIs (Mission Related Investments) philanthropists can maintain rights over Nature-based Solution Credits (type of carbon credit) for up to 5 years through renewable legal contracts to extract usufruct rights to sequester carbon. The new programs deliver new promise for the organization and a sustainable solution to climate change by providing ecosystem services from the natural heritage of some of the world's most endangered civilizations.
